Retired Lt Col Richard 'Dick' Cole and Staff Sgt David Thacker presented the Congressional Gold Medal to the National Museum of the US Air Force on Saturday . 
  The medal was awarded by Congress for their daring bombing attack on Japan on April 18, 1942 . 
  The raid boosted American morale in the wake of Pearl Harbor attack  . 
  The medal will be on permanent display at the museum . 
 